1 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.229-8 of Title 70, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. As part of the comprehensive, integrated curriculum for
5 substance abuse programs provided in Section 1210.229-5 of Title 70
6 of the Oklahoma Statutes, each school district shall annually
7 provide research-based instruction related to fentanyl abuse
8 prevention and drug poisoning awareness to students in grades six
9 through twelve.
10 B. The instruction required by this section shall include:
11 1. Suicide prevention;
12 2. Prevention of the abuse of and addiction to fentanyl;
13 3. Awareness of local school and community resources and how to
14 access those resources; and
15 4. Health education that includes information about substance
16 use and abuse of fentanyl, including youth substance use and abuse
17 of fentanyl.
18 C. The instruction required by this section may be provided by
19 an organization or an employee or agent of an organization that is:
20 1. A public or private institution of higher education;
21 2. A library;
22 3. A community service organization;
23 4. A religious organization;
24 5. A local public health agency; or
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1484 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 6. An organization employing mental health professionals.
2 D. The State Board of Education shall identify and adopt
3 curriculum standards for fentanyl awareness instruction that reflect
4 the areas of instruction listed in subsection B of this section.
5 The standards shall be incorporated into the appropriate health
6 standards for grades six through twelve.
7 E. The State Department of Education shall provide resources to
8 assist schools and teachers in providing instruction on fentanyl
9 awareness.
10 F. Any school district that offers a health education class in
11 grades six through twelve shall include fentanyl awareness
12 curriculum in the drug awareness unit.
13 G. To educate students about the dangers posed by fentanyl and
14 the risks of fentanyl poisoning, including overdose, the Governor
15 shall designate a week to be known as Fentanyl Poisoning Awareness
16 Week in public schools. Fentanyl Poisoning Awareness Week shall be
17 in correlation with National Red Ribbon Week. Fentanyl Poisoning
18 Awareness Week may include age-appropriate instruction, including
19 instruction on the prevention of the abuse of and addiction to
20 fentanyl, as determined by each school district.
21 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
22 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
